    "attributes": {
        "action": "Launch a national public awareness campaign about knife crime",
        "additional_details": "Knife crime has increased in recent years and we believe the only way to slow the growth is to send a clear a message.\r\n \r\nThere were 46,239 police recorded offences involving a knife or sharp instrument in England and Wales in the 12 months to September 2021.\r\n",
        "background": "The campaign should be focused on youth crime and gangs, showing how the consequences of knife crime ruins lives, both of the victim, their family, friends and the perpetrator.",
